 from design, to manufacturing, to creation of hardware and firmware (usually
 in C++ or Python), and finally to integration in data anlysis databases
 that we keep at the lab.
 I have spanned the gamut of engineering in the creation of these detectors,
 from the drawings required for manufacturing - for which I use Solidworks,
 comparisons to ANSI specifications, to calculations on their efficiency
 and other figures of merit.
 I've attained good effect through these skills: a presentation in the Instrumen
tation and Controls session about the results achieved by the detectors
 won the 2016 American Nuclear Society Young Members' Group Best Paper Award.
